{"word":"αἴτημα","slug":"αἴτημα","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b><el>αἴτημα, ατος, τό</el></b> [<el><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:αἰτέω\">αἰτέω</a></el>] ‘that which has been requested’, <b><i>request, petition</i> <a href='B:570 4:6'>Phil 4:6</a>; <a href='B:690 5:15'>1 J 5:15</a>.</b> The context of <b><a href='B:490 23:24'>Lk 23:24</a></b> is best served by the rendering <b><i>demand.</i></b> <center id=\"nav_bottom\"> <a id=\"left_arrow\" href=\"S:αἰτέω\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> <a id=\"bottom_home\" href=\"S:#1.Table of Contents\">&emsp;&emsp;</a> <a id=\"right_arrow\" href=\"S:αἰτία\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> </center> "}]}